author: Staff Reports
title: Local Roundup: Oakdale boys, girls blank TJ
text:
Boys Soccer 
Oakdale 2, TJ 0 
Anthony Kocan and Brendan Ziegler each had a goal for visiting Oakdale (6-2-1, 1-1 CMC Spires), as both were assisted by Bryce Currie on Thursday night. 
Dakota Harich recorded the shutout with four saves. 
Sam Roy had six saves for Thomas Johnson (4-4-1, 1-1). 
TJ won the junior varsity match 3-0. 
Girls Soccer 
Hannah Orland had 10 saves for Thomas Johnson. 
Urbana 4, Middletown 2 
Erin Scarborough and Maggie Poletti each had a goal for Middletown (4-5). Kaitlyn Ridenour had one assist for the Knights. 
Sarah Durham and Cortney Renninger combined for seven saves for Middletown. 
No information was provided for Urbana. 
Middletown won the junior varsity match 1-0. 
Volleyball 
Linganore 3, Brunswick 0 
Scores: 25-10, 25-12, 25-19. Linganore leaders: Brooke Hayden, 9 kills; Eva Rowan, 10 digs, 6 kills; Hannah Laughter, 11 digs; Maddie France, 16 assists, 11 digs; Sarah Zentz, 3 blocks. Brunswick leaders: Hannah Buhr, 6 kills; Jennifer Barbot, 5 kills; Kori Payne, 9 digs. JV: Linganore. 
Tuscarora 3, Frederick 0 
Scores: 25-7, 25-9, 25-10. Tuscarora leaders: Maddie Roat, 9 aces, 7 kills; Ysabel Weaver, 16 assists; Zarah White, 11 digs; Molly Weaver, 10 aces, 6 digs, 6 kills. Frederick leaders: Dajah Gee, 3 kills, 2 blocks; Jarin Pruce, 9 digs; Caroline Strakonsky, 7 digs. JV: Tuscarora, 2-1. 
Oakdale 3, TJ 0 
Scores: 25-19, 25-11, 25-14. Oakdale leaders: Abbie Harry, 15 kills, 9 digs, 2 blocks; Eleanor Saylor, 6 kills, 9 digs; Jamie Humphrey, 12 digs; Valeria Retana, 15 assists, 6 digs; Morgan Humphries, 11 assists. Oakdale record: 4-3. JV: TJ, 2-1. 
Urbana 3, Boonsboro 0 
Scores: 21-25, 25-23, 24-26, 25-11, 15-6. Urbana leaders: Kylie Hayes, 18 kills; Darian DiMatteo, 9 kills; Hannah Goodacre, 34 assists; Marci Senires, 8 blocks, 6 kills; Natalie Perez, 11 digs. 
Golf 
Middletown 160, Walkersville 205 
Jake Darr shot a 37 for Middletown (10-2) at Maryland National Golf Club. Andrew Heon shot 40. 
Sam Driscoll shot 41 for Walkersville. 
Tuscarora 181, Oakdale 202 
The Titans (6-3) were led by Kaillin Hughes and Nick Fox, who each shot a 43 at Worthington Manor. 
College Volleyball 
FCC 3, NOVA 0 
FCC leaders: Amy Gust, 8 kills; Emily Rabat, 6 kills, 5 aces; Tori Bryant, 25 assists; Victoria Ketner, 9 digs; Haley Gieck, 9 digs. FCC record: 16-1. 
JV Football 
Catoctin 25, Brunswick 0: The Cougars’ Christian Michael tossed touchdown passes to Chad Gerrie and Nick Reaver on Wednesday, while Noah Shriner and Chase Wilhelm each ran for a score. Justin Reaver kick an extra point. ×
